WEBVTT

00:06.041 --> 00:10.791
- ["La Vie en Rose" playing]
<i>- ♪ Hold me close and hold me fast ♪</i>

00:10.791 --> 00:13.666
<i>♪ This magic spell you cast ♪</i>

00:13.666 --> 00:18.000
<i>♪ This is</i> la vie en rose <i>♪</i>

00:18.500 --> 00:21.833
<i>- ♪ When you kiss me, heaven sighs ♪</i>
- [echoing] Camille!

00:21.833 --> 00:24.583
<i>♪ And though I close my eyes ♪</i>

00:24.583 --> 00:28.291
<i>- ♪ I see</i> la vie en rose <i>♪</i>
- Camille!

00:28.291 --> 00:30.916
[laughs] Camille! I can't believe it!

00:30.916 --> 00:33.166
What an amazing coincidence.
It's unbelievable.

00:33.166 --> 00:35.083
I'm staying in this hotel.

00:35.083 --> 00:38.083
Well, in any case,
I kept thinking about our conversation,

00:38.083 --> 00:40.000
and I couldn't get it out of my head.

00:40.000 --> 00:42.625
And I started thinking,
maybe you thought I was rude or impolite.

00:42.625 --> 00:45.666
- Because I left so suddenly, and--
- [horn honks]

00:45.666 --> 00:47.291
["La Vie en Rose" fades]

00:47.291 --> 00:50.000
If you let me, I can explain everything.

00:50.000 --> 00:52.375
It's just that... [takes a deep breath]

00:52.375 --> 00:55.041
Well, I just got divorced,
and I had promised myself--

00:55.041 --> 00:57.166
- I'd love to hear about that promise.
- Okay.

00:57.166 --> 00:59.166
- Now it's me that might seem rude--
- Getting in?

00:59.166 --> 01:01.833
Yes, yes. Yes.
To be honest, I'm in a real hurry.

01:01.833 --> 01:04.791
- I'm late for a concert.
- In that case, why don't I come with you?

01:04.791 --> 01:07.291
- And we can chat a little on the way.
- [horn honks]

01:09.583 --> 01:12.041
[upbeat music playing]

01:22.291 --> 01:24.125
[upbeat music fades]

01:25.250 --> 01:26.791
- [sighs]
- [rapping on door]

01:28.250 --> 01:29.166
[Roi] Come in.

01:30.166 --> 01:31.291
Bring the bike?

01:33.958 --> 01:34.833
The keys, please.

01:34.833 --> 01:36.250
Where you going?

01:37.458 --> 01:39.833
I have something to do.
An errand for Berlin.

01:39.833 --> 01:41.083
The keys, please.

01:42.041 --> 01:43.583
[sultry music playing]

01:45.375 --> 01:46.708
[clicks tongue]

01:46.708 --> 01:48.375
[softly] Where are you going?

01:48.375 --> 01:50.166
I have to get the chalice.

01:50.166 --> 01:53.500
And in the meantime,
you stay here and watch the monitors.

01:53.500 --> 01:54.416
Hmm?

01:56.208 --> 01:57.041
[sighs]

01:58.583 --> 02:00.875
But there's no one at home, idiot.

02:01.458 --> 02:05.125
- In case they come back.
- And how do you expect to get the chalice?

02:06.291 --> 02:07.500
I wait for the priest,

02:07.500 --> 02:09.000
I start the bike,

02:09.000 --> 02:10.291
I drive by,

02:10.291 --> 02:12.041
I grab it, and ciao.

02:12.666 --> 02:13.500
Capisce?

02:13.500 --> 02:16.000
And which hand will you use to grab it?

02:16.000 --> 02:18.083
I already know you're good
with your hands,

02:18.083 --> 02:19.916
but that chalice is pretty heavy.

02:19.916 --> 02:21.708
You're trying the briefcase pull?

02:22.500 --> 02:25.041
- [Roi sighs]
- I'm coming with you, and that's that.

02:25.041 --> 02:27.000
And anyway, fast bikes are my thing.

02:28.791 --> 02:31.791
[energetic music playing]

02:40.666 --> 02:41.500
[music fades]

02:41.500 --> 02:43.208
[Berlin] Well, how can I put this? Um...

02:43.208 --> 02:45.791
I promised myself
that I would... take a break

02:45.791 --> 02:47.791
and not see anyone for a little while.

02:47.791 --> 02:49.416
Do you mind if I get dressed?

02:49.416 --> 02:51.500
I brought some clothes
to change into on the way.

02:51.500 --> 02:54.041
- [whimsical music playing]
- But of course. Yes. Be my guest.

02:54.041 --> 02:56.708
Um, I was looking forward to...

02:56.708 --> 02:59.416
to enjoying some time on my own.

02:59.416 --> 03:00.708
A life of solitude.

03:00.708 --> 03:04.666
You see, what my heart needs
is time to find peace.

03:04.666 --> 03:06.583
Don't you think that sounds misogynistic?

03:06.583 --> 03:08.041
No. [chuckles] No. Not at all.

03:08.041 --> 03:12.000
Personally, I find it's more a question
of self-preservation.

03:12.000 --> 03:16.333
But then, after our conversation,
I began to wonder.

03:16.333 --> 03:20.208
What if I'm punishing myself
for a failed marriage, huh?

03:20.208 --> 03:23.416
Am I, in fact, denying myself
the opportunity of meeting

03:23.416 --> 03:24.791
a marvelous woman?

03:25.500 --> 03:27.958
There are four billion women
on this planet.

03:29.000 --> 03:32.041
The chances of meeting someone
truly fascinating are quite slim.

03:32.041 --> 03:34.375
And to ignore
such a chance is unacceptable.

03:34.375 --> 03:37.833
And that's why I called out
to you like a madman on the street.

03:37.833 --> 03:39.958
I mean, what are
the chances we would ever...

03:39.958 --> 03:40.875
May I?

03:40.875 --> 03:42.333
- Yes?
- ...meet?

03:44.125 --> 03:46.125
And... and that's why I'm here.

03:46.125 --> 03:47.666
[laughs]

03:47.666 --> 03:49.833
[chuckles softly]

03:51.750 --> 03:53.791
[whimsical music fades]

03:53.791 --> 03:54.916
[Camille] Thanks.

03:54.916 --> 03:57.166
[indistinct, excited chatter]

03:57.166 --> 03:58.083
Hey!

03:58.791 --> 04:00.958
- [Camille laughs]
- And don't forget what I said.

04:00.958 --> 04:02.708
[heavy distortion building]

04:05.625 --> 04:08.125
[punk rock music playing]

04:08.125 --> 04:10.000
[punk rock music fades]

04:10.000 --> 04:11.291
["Bullets and Flowers" playing]

04:12.791 --> 04:15.875
<i>♪ True love and flowers ♪</i>

04:17.958 --> 04:20.375
<i>♪ Bullets instead ♪</i>

04:20.875 --> 04:23.666
<i>♪ Breaking through my chest ♪</i>

04:23.666 --> 04:27.125
<i>♪ Would you ever cry for me? ♪</i>

04:27.125 --> 04:29.875
<i>♪ There is no other way ♪</i>

04:29.875 --> 04:32.666
<i>♪ There is nothing I can say ♪</i>

04:32.666 --> 04:35.083
<i>♪ Gonna pray for all I did ♪</i>

04:35.083 --> 04:38.125
<i>♪ I will beg down on my knees ♪</i>

04:38.125 --> 04:39.916
<i>♪ Never knew to draw the line ♪</i>

04:39.916 --> 04:43.666
<i>♪ Too many troubles on my mind ♪</i>

04:43.666 --> 04:46.333
<i>♪ No regret that I can give ♪</i>

04:46.333 --> 04:48.750
<i>♪ But someday I will forgive ♪</i>

04:48.750 --> 04:51.458
<i>♪ Myself ♪</i>

04:51.958 --> 04:54.083
[theme song fades]

04:54.083 --> 04:55.833
[tense music playing]

05:02.791 --> 05:03.875
[Roi] Let's go.

05:04.375 --> 05:06.375
[engine revs]

05:06.375 --> 05:08.291
- Stop, stop, stop!
- [brakes screech]

05:08.291 --> 05:10.666
[Roi] He's with those guys, those ex-cons.

05:13.625 --> 05:15.250
[speaking inaudibly]

05:20.500 --> 05:21.333
Taxi!

05:23.375 --> 05:24.958
[gasps] Go!

05:26.250 --> 05:27.750
[engine revs]

05:28.416 --> 05:29.541
[Toureaux yelps]

05:29.541 --> 05:30.916
[screaming]

05:30.916 --> 05:33.875
- [Roi] Shit! He won't let go!
- [in French] Victor! Father Toureaux!

05:33.875 --> 05:35.250
[rock music playing]

05:35.250 --> 05:36.375
[grunts]

05:36.375 --> 05:37.500
[music cuts out]

05:40.250 --> 05:41.708
[gasps, in English] The chalice!

05:41.708 --> 05:44.083
- [Roi] Grab the bag!
- [Toureaux] The chalice!

05:45.833 --> 05:47.750
- [groans]
- [tense music continues]

05:49.666 --> 05:51.125
[Toureaux] The chalice! [coughs]

05:51.125 --> 05:52.375
[grunts]

05:52.375 --> 05:54.000
- [Toureaux] Victor!
- [engine revs]

05:54.000 --> 05:55.125
[both panting]

05:56.333 --> 05:58.166
Hurry up! Come on!

05:58.166 --> 05:59.958
[grunts] Fucking get them!

05:59.958 --> 06:01.333
[both panting]

06:02.458 --> 06:04.458
[tense music building]

06:08.041 --> 06:09.083
[tires squeal]

06:09.083 --> 06:10.625
- [music fades]
- [church bells ringing]

06:10.625 --> 06:13.958
- [romantic string quartet playing]
- [guests exclaim]

06:16.375 --> 06:18.041
[guests cheer]

06:18.958 --> 06:21.083
[tense, rhythmic music resumes]

06:21.083 --> 06:22.250
[engine revs]

06:22.833 --> 06:23.916
[Roi] Move!

06:24.041 --> 06:26.541
- [screaming]
- [Roi] Get out of the fuckin' way!

06:28.916 --> 06:30.666
[guests clamoring]

06:31.708 --> 06:32.625
[engine revs]

06:32.625 --> 06:33.958
[Cameron] Roi!

06:35.083 --> 06:36.958
What are you doing? [yelps]

06:40.333 --> 06:42.333
- Are you okay?
- [motorcycle approaching]

06:43.750 --> 06:44.583
[brakes screech]

06:44.583 --> 06:46.791
- [shouts]
- Step on it!

06:47.458 --> 06:49.083
[engine revs]

06:49.083 --> 06:50.166
Get outta the fucking way!

06:50.166 --> 06:52.083
Move, for fuck's sake!

06:52.083 --> 06:54.208
- Are you crazy?
- Shut the fuck up!

06:54.208 --> 06:56.083
- What's wrong with my wife?
- What's going on?

06:56.083 --> 06:57.375
Move your ass! Quick!

06:57.375 --> 06:59.791
- [shouting]
- [quartet tempo increases]

06:59.791 --> 07:00.958
[Roi groans]

07:00.958 --> 07:02.083
[Cameron] Shit!

07:02.083 --> 07:03.875
- Move your ass, lady!
- No!

07:03.875 --> 07:05.375
- Move your ass!
- Hey!

07:05.375 --> 07:07.333
- I won't ask again!
- [Victor] Enough!

07:07.333 --> 07:10.916
[punk rock version
of "What a Wonderful World" playing]

07:10.916 --> 07:13.125
<i>- ♪ I see trees of green ♪</i>
- Son of a bitch!

07:13.791 --> 07:16.208
<i>♪ Red roses too ♪</i>

07:16.208 --> 07:18.958
- [crowd cheers]
<i>- ♪ I see them bloom ♪</i>

07:19.458 --> 07:21.125
<i>♪ For me and you ♪</i>

07:21.125 --> 07:24.125
<i>♪ And I think to myself ♪</i>

07:25.791 --> 07:28.791
<i>♪ What a wonderful world ♪</i>

07:30.708 --> 07:32.833
<i>♪ The colors of the rainbow ♪</i>

07:32.833 --> 07:36.125
<i>♪ Are so pretty in the sky ♪</i>

07:36.125 --> 07:39.000
<i>♪ Are also on the faces ♪</i>

07:39.000 --> 07:41.625
<i>♪ Of people walkin' by ♪</i>

07:41.625 --> 07:44.333
<i>♪ I see friends shakin' hands ♪</i>

07:44.333 --> 07:47.291
<i>♪ Sayin', "How do you do?" ♪</i>

07:48.125 --> 07:50.791
<i>♪ They're really sayin' ♪</i>

07:50.791 --> 07:52.791
<i>♪ "I love you" ♪</i>

07:52.791 --> 07:56.041
<i>♪ I see babies cry ♪</i>

07:57.083 --> 07:58.708
<i>♪ I watch them grow ♪</i>

07:59.458 --> 08:01.333
<i>♪ They learn much more ♪</i>

08:01.333 --> 08:04.375
<i>♪ Than I'll ever know ♪</i>

08:04.375 --> 08:07.458
<i>♪ And I think to myself ♪</i>

08:07.458 --> 08:08.791
[crowd cheering]

08:08.791 --> 08:11.916
<i>- ♪ What a wonderful world ♪</i>
- [singing along]

08:12.916 --> 08:16.375
<i>♪ And I say to myself ♪</i>

08:17.458 --> 08:21.416
<i>♪ What a wonderful world ♪</i>

08:21.416 --> 08:23.750
[crowd cheering]

08:26.083 --> 08:27.291
[song ends]

08:27.291 --> 08:30.416
[cheers and laughter echo]

08:32.541 --> 08:34.958
[suspenseful music playing]

08:34.958 --> 08:36.708
Table! Watch out! Shit!

08:37.750 --> 08:39.833
- For fuck's sake!
- Faster!

08:39.833 --> 08:41.875
Roi, shut the fuck up! Just shut it! Okay?

08:42.708 --> 08:43.875
Watch out! Watch out!

08:43.875 --> 08:45.208
[screams]

08:45.208 --> 08:47.708
- [tires squeal]
- [Roi] Watch out!

08:47.708 --> 08:49.083
[mourners murmur]

08:50.500 --> 08:52.041
A wedding and a funeral.

08:52.041 --> 08:53.416
Just like the movie.

08:53.416 --> 08:54.666
[tense music playing]

08:54.666 --> 08:55.583
[Roi] Look.

08:56.625 --> 08:58.000
[engine revs]

09:02.750 --> 09:04.250
- [horn honks]
- [driver] Hey!

09:08.708 --> 09:10.166
- [man] Watch it!
- [shouting]

09:11.000 --> 09:12.333
[man] Asshole!

09:19.041 --> 09:20.666
[tense music fades]

09:20.666 --> 09:22.041
[both panting]

09:23.000 --> 09:24.916
- [Cameron] This way.
- [bike approaching]

09:26.875 --> 09:28.916
- [tires squeal]
- [Cameron] Get down.

09:31.750 --> 09:33.333
[suspenseful music playing]

09:35.833 --> 09:36.958
[Victor] The fuck are they?

09:36.958 --> 09:38.333
Come out, you bastards!

09:39.666 --> 09:40.916
You're dead!

09:41.416 --> 09:42.916
If we move, they'll hear us for sure.

09:45.541 --> 09:47.166
Not if we create a diversion.

09:48.291 --> 09:49.875
Hold on. Hold on. Hold on.

09:49.875 --> 09:51.916
- I heard something.
- [sighs]

09:53.041 --> 09:54.000
[Roi exhales]

09:54.958 --> 09:57.458
Meet me at spot 123. Go that way.

09:57.458 --> 09:58.708
Follow my lead.

10:00.833 --> 10:03.291
[suspenseful, rhythmic music playing]

10:06.416 --> 10:08.125
[car alarms go off]

10:09.333 --> 10:10.500
[Victor] Hey!

10:11.000 --> 10:12.375
What is that?

10:15.833 --> 10:16.750
[sighs]

10:17.416 --> 10:18.916
[alarm wailing]

10:20.375 --> 10:21.583
[Victor] The hell's going on?

10:22.541 --> 10:25.083
- [alarm blaring]
- What the fuck is this shit?!

10:25.875 --> 10:27.666
- Go check there.
- [Victor] Okay.

10:27.666 --> 10:28.958
[alarms blaring]

10:31.708 --> 10:33.791
Come on. Show yourselves.

10:36.708 --> 10:37.875
Dammit!

10:52.125 --> 10:54.166
- [Roi] Hey!
- Shit! [gasps]

10:54.666 --> 10:56.458
- You okay?
- Now what?

10:56.458 --> 10:58.416
We hot-wire a car and make a run.

10:58.416 --> 11:01.083
But it has to be an old car
with no alarm system.

11:01.083 --> 11:02.250
Like that one.

11:02.250 --> 11:04.166
- [exhales]
- You ready?

11:05.416 --> 11:07.208
[suspenseful music continues]

11:13.041 --> 11:14.166
[doors close]

11:19.166 --> 11:21.416
- [electricity crackles]
- [alarm blares]

11:21.416 --> 11:23.375
- Shit!
- Start the damn car!

11:23.375 --> 11:25.541
I can't. The alarm's gone off.
The ignition won't work.

11:25.541 --> 11:27.333
- So what now?
- [Roi] They're coming.

11:28.416 --> 11:29.666
Get in the back.

11:30.333 --> 11:31.208
Move it.

11:33.291 --> 11:35.083
[suspenseful music swells]

11:36.083 --> 11:37.666
[music stops abruptly]

11:38.583 --> 11:41.000
[tense music continues]

11:48.541 --> 11:50.166
[tense music building]

11:52.500 --> 11:53.708
[music ends]

11:53.708 --> 11:56.083
[Camille] I didn't think
you'd be able to fit in here.

11:56.083 --> 11:58.916
But then, you jumped straight in. [laughs]

11:58.916 --> 12:00.083
It's my bow tie.

12:01.208 --> 12:03.333
I like to be elegant,
even when I'm grocery shopping.

12:03.333 --> 12:04.291
[both laugh]

12:04.291 --> 12:07.375
You really don't look like
the kind of man who goes shopping.

12:08.041 --> 12:11.125
You look like the kind of man
who lives in hotels.

12:11.125 --> 12:14.500
Who travels around the world
and visits museums.

12:14.500 --> 12:17.083
And likes vintage wines
from French châteaus.

12:18.750 --> 12:20.875
[laughs] Mm.

12:20.875 --> 12:23.083
[tender instrumental music playing]

12:28.375 --> 12:31.583
I bet you this is the very first time
you drank beer from a bottle.

12:31.583 --> 12:33.416
[both laugh]

12:33.416 --> 12:34.333
You're right.

12:34.333 --> 12:37.208
I hate drinking
from bottles that have traveled in crates

12:37.208 --> 12:40.583
and are moved from warehouses from trucks
and from people's hands to our lips.

12:40.583 --> 12:41.750
It's revolting.

12:41.750 --> 12:43.916
But this one tastes glorious. [laughs]

12:43.916 --> 12:45.166
Let's drink to that.

12:45.166 --> 12:46.916
To tasting glorious.

12:46.916 --> 12:49.291
[indistinct chatter]

12:49.291 --> 12:51.291
[alarms blaring]

12:52.875 --> 12:54.000
Are they still there?

12:54.000 --> 12:56.958
- [tense music playing]
- [breathing shakily]

12:56.958 --> 13:00.291
I don't see them,
but we're not waiting here to find out.

13:02.125 --> 13:03.875
Let's try that car. [grunts]

13:06.750 --> 13:08.500
[Cameron panting]

13:08.500 --> 13:10.083
- [crackles]
- [engine starts]

13:10.083 --> 13:12.250
- Fuck yeah!
- Go, go, go! C'mon! Move it!

13:15.000 --> 13:17.458
- [shouts] There you are, thief!
- [Roi] Shit!

13:17.458 --> 13:19.291
- Fuckin' thief!
- Faster, Roi! Faster!

13:22.083 --> 13:23.250
[tires squeal]

13:23.833 --> 13:25.041
Careful! Watch out!

13:26.166 --> 13:28.041
[horn blares]

13:28.041 --> 13:30.166
[Roi groans]

13:32.458 --> 13:33.875
[Cameron grunts]

13:34.375 --> 13:36.083
[tense music pulsing]

13:40.958 --> 13:43.125
[tense music swells]

13:46.916 --> 13:47.791
Oh shit.

13:47.791 --> 13:50.125
[tense music building]

13:50.125 --> 13:51.291
Fuck.

13:58.041 --> 13:59.000
[Roi moans]

14:05.875 --> 14:07.458
[both panting]

14:13.000 --> 14:14.000
[Roi] Let's go.

14:14.000 --> 14:15.333
[Cameron grunts]

14:16.500 --> 14:18.208
[both panting]

14:18.208 --> 14:20.166
That's it. Run, you bitch.

14:21.958 --> 14:23.083
Go on. Run, you pussies.

14:25.375 --> 14:28.416
[dramatic string music playing]

14:39.833 --> 14:42.875
[dramatic music fades]

14:44.583 --> 14:46.916
["Goosebumps and Butterflies" playing
on taxi stereo]

14:50.375 --> 14:52.625
<i>♪ Every little thing you do ♪</i>

14:52.625 --> 14:55.875
<i>♪ Every little word you say ♪</i>

14:55.875 --> 14:58.458
<i>♪ Make me want to come with you ♪</i>

14:58.458 --> 15:00.541
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

15:00.541 --> 15:04.333
<i>♪ You give me goosebumps ♪</i>

15:05.041 --> 15:06.416
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪</i>

15:06.416 --> 15:10.583
<i>♪ You give me goosebumps and butterflies ♪</i>

15:10.583 --> 15:12.083
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪</i>

15:12.083 --> 15:15.458
<i>♪ You give me goosebumps ♪</i>

15:16.375 --> 15:17.958
<i>- ♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪</i>
- [song fades]

15:17.958 --> 15:19.541
[both chuckle softly]

15:19.541 --> 15:20.625
[Camille chuckles]

15:20.625 --> 15:23.500
I just wanna thank you
for... a wonderful evening.

15:23.500 --> 15:26.000
- Extraordinary, even. [chuckles]
- [Berlin] Mm.

15:26.500 --> 15:31.208
Um, I sincerely hope we can do this again
the next time I'm back in Paris.

15:31.208 --> 15:34.833
The next time, I'll take you someplace
where you can drink from Bohemia crystal.

15:34.833 --> 15:37.208
[chuckles] Well, in that case,
you'll need my phone number.

15:39.541 --> 15:41.458
Unfortunately, I don't have a pen.

15:45.458 --> 15:46.916
[gentle music playing]

16:01.541 --> 16:04.333
[gentle music swells]

16:25.083 --> 16:26.458
[softly] Good night.

16:26.458 --> 16:28.041
Sleep tight.

16:30.083 --> 16:32.458
[gentle music continues]

