- [sounds distort]
- [shuddering exhale]

33:20.958 --> 33:22.666
All I can see is the name.

33:22.666 --> 33:24.250
- Always.
- What name?

33:24.250 --> 33:27.291
"Lobo." That's the Spanish word for wolf.

33:27.291 --> 33:29.166
"Lobo, Lobo, Lobo, Lobo, Lobo."

33:29.166 --> 33:31.875
And now something
very unusual has happened.

33:31.875 --> 33:33.375
He slapped your ass?

33:33.375 --> 33:35.208
- Don't be silly.
- [laughs]

33:35.791 --> 33:39.833
[sighs] It looks like...
like I've become addicted to his scent.

33:40.500 --> 33:42.000
Huh. What do you mean?

33:42.000 --> 33:43.625
I can smell him.

33:44.125 --> 33:48.291
Whenever I'm near him,
whenever he walks by, I smell him.

33:48.291 --> 33:50.208
What smell? His cologne?

33:50.208 --> 33:51.916
No, I don't think he uses cologne.

33:51.916 --> 33:55.291
It's something like... uh...

33:55.291 --> 33:57.000
A <i>male</i> scent.

33:57.000 --> 33:58.583
Like a wild beast.

33:58.583 --> 33:59.791
Like pheromones.

33:59.791 --> 34:00.750
I don't know.

34:00.750 --> 34:01.958
Girl, it's his sweat.

34:01.958 --> 34:04.583
It must be sweat,
but I've always found sweat disgusting.

34:04.583 --> 34:06.750
But when Bruce walks by...
[inhales deeply]

34:06.750 --> 34:08.375
[inhale echoes]

34:08.375 --> 34:11.375
- [bright instrumental music playing]
- [exhales slowly]

34:11.375 --> 34:13.916
- [dramatically] I inhale.
- [bright music fades]

34:15.208 --> 34:16.583
You... inhale?

34:20.791 --> 34:22.291
[whimsical music playing]

34:23.958 --> 34:25.583
- He wiped himself with this.
- Keila.

34:25.583 --> 34:28.041
I was going to wash it
with my laundry, but I didn't.

34:28.041 --> 34:31.416
What's wrong with me, Cameron?
I don't understand these impulses.

34:31.916 --> 34:33.500
Relax. Stop being so dramatic.

34:33.500 --> 34:35.333
What's wrong with having a crush on Bruce?

34:35.333 --> 34:38.083
I don't know.
I mean, the guy's just a baby.

34:38.083 --> 34:39.833
What age is he? Twenty-four?

34:39.833 --> 34:41.166
I'm 36 years old.

34:42.375 --> 34:43.333
Help.

34:44.916 --> 34:45.916
Well...

34:47.375 --> 34:50.125
if you feel like getting laid,
then just do it.

34:50.916 --> 34:52.041
And then forget about it.

34:52.041 --> 34:53.833
But if it means trouble,
then don't go there.

34:53.833 --> 34:56.666
Sex is fun,
but love's a very different story.

34:56.666 --> 34:58.250
Why do you say that, Cameron?

34:58.750 --> 35:00.208
[somber piano music playing]

35:00.208 --> 35:03.541
Love is a disease with different phases.

35:04.500 --> 35:05.958
Anxiety when you find it.

35:06.458 --> 35:07.833
Fear of losing it.

35:08.916 --> 35:10.541
Depression when it leaves you.

35:13.916 --> 35:14.958
[exhales]

35:17.166 --> 35:20.875
Keila, you know what I do
when I get really upset about stuff?

35:20.875 --> 35:22.958
- What?
- I dance.

35:27.166 --> 35:28.125
Why would you do that?

35:28.125 --> 35:29.458
[loud pop music playing]

35:29.458 --> 35:31.750
[Cameron] Come on. Get up.
We're gonna have a party.

35:31.750 --> 35:33.416
["I Love It" by Icona Pop playing]

35:33.416 --> 35:35.166
Come on, Keila! [laughs]

35:35.166 --> 35:36.291
You're crazy.

35:36.291 --> 35:38.458
- Come on, Kei-Kei. Let's go!
- No! No way!

35:38.458 --> 35:40.500
<i>♪ On the summer day when you were gone ♪</i>

35:40.500 --> 35:42.500
<i>♪ I crashed my car into the bridge... ♪</i>

35:42.500 --> 35:44.250
- [Keila] I can't dance. No!
- C'mon Keila!

35:44.250 --> 35:45.958
- I don't drink. Ever.
- Go for it!

35:45.958 --> 35:47.750
- Open wide, girl.
- [coughs]

35:47.750 --> 35:48.958
[laughs]

35:48.958 --> 35:50.250
<i>♪ Into the bridge ♪</i>

35:50.250 --> 35:52.625
<i>♪ I don't care ♪</i>

35:52.625 --> 35:54.083
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

35:54.083 --> 35:56.000
<i>♪ I don't care ♪</i>

35:58.500 --> 36:02.125
<i>♪ I got this feeling
On the summer day when you were gone ♪</i>

36:02.125 --> 36:03.958
<i>♪ I crashed my car into the bridge ♪</i>

36:03.958 --> 36:05.625
<i>♪ I watched, I let it burn ♪</i>

36:05.625 --> 36:07.875
<i>♪ I threw your shit into a bag... ♪</i>

36:08.458 --> 36:09.583
[knocking on door]

36:09.583 --> 36:11.458
<i>♪ I crashed my car into the bridge ♪</i>

36:11.458 --> 36:14.125
[on speaker] <i>♪ I don't care ♪</i>

36:14.125 --> 36:15.166
What's all this?

36:15.166 --> 36:17.041
- That music?
- Yeah, but we were going to bed.

36:17.041 --> 36:18.000
Bruce!

36:18.000 --> 36:19.583
[beat pulsing]

36:19.583 --> 36:21.416
<i>♪ You're on a different road ♪</i>

36:21.416 --> 36:23.791
- [sounds distort and dampen]
<i>- ♪ I'm in the Milky Way ♪</i>

36:23.791 --> 36:25.625
<i>♪ You want me down on earth ♪</i>

36:25.625 --> 36:27.500
<i>♪ But I am up in space ♪</i>

36:27.500 --> 36:31.250
<i>♪ You're so damn hard to please
We gotta kill this switch ♪</i>

36:31.250 --> 36:32.583
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

36:35.916 --> 36:38.250
Houston, we have a problem.

36:38.875 --> 36:39.708
I'm on it.

36:40.750 --> 36:43.000
- [music cuts out]
- [phone ringing]

36:43.000 --> 36:44.375
[girls laughing]

36:44.375 --> 36:45.291
Yo!

36:45.291 --> 36:46.750
- No way. Take 'em.
- [Bruce] Come on.

36:46.750 --> 36:48.916
- Join us.
- Roi! [laughs]

36:50.166 --> 36:52.416
- Okay. Just one.
- That's it.

36:53.916 --> 36:57.916
<i>♪ I got this feeling on the summer day
When you were gone ♪</i>

36:57.916 --> 37:00.000
<i>♪ I crashed my car into the bridge ♪</i>

37:00.000 --> 37:01.583
<i>♪ I watched, I let it burn ♪</i>

37:01.583 --> 37:03.666
<i>♪ I threw your shit into a bag ♪</i>

37:03.666 --> 37:05.791
<i>♪ And pushed it down the stairs ♪</i>

37:05.791 --> 37:08.208
<i>♪ I crashed my car into the bridge ♪</i>

37:08.208 --> 37:09.708
<i>♪ I don't care ♪</i>

37:09.708 --> 37:11.291
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

37:11.291 --> 37:13.375
<i>♪ I don't care ♪</i>

37:13.375 --> 37:15.125
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

37:15.125 --> 37:17.416
- <i>♪ I love it ♪</i>
- <i>♪ I don't care ♪</i>

37:23.708 --> 37:24.958
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

37:24.958 --> 37:27.166
[laughter echoes, fades]

37:27.166 --> 37:28.916
[sounds distort and echo]

37:28.916 --> 37:30.208
[exhales]

37:30.208 --> 37:31.541
Are you okay?

37:32.416 --> 37:34.875
I kinda feel like... throwing up.

37:34.875 --> 37:36.166
Oh, Kei-Kei.

37:40.583 --> 37:42.375
[shouting] Hey! How are we doing?

37:45.166 --> 37:47.291
- We made it!
- [energetic music playing]

37:47.291 --> 37:50.291
Work on the tunnel will be completed
when we reach a brick wall

37:50.291 --> 37:52.333
that will lead us to our goal.

37:52.833 --> 37:54.791
The Viénot Auction House.

37:55.291 --> 37:56.541
And what's that wall?

37:56.541 --> 37:58.541
It's the retaining wall of the building.

37:58.541 --> 38:00.666
We break through it
to get inside the auction house.

38:04.416 --> 38:07.458
But instead of getting into the vault
through the main steel doors,

38:08.291 --> 38:10.083
<i>we go through the back door.</i>

38:10.083 --> 38:12.166
No one expects that. [laughs]

38:14.375 --> 38:17.166
And in order to get access
to the back door,

38:17.166 --> 38:19.958
first, we move
into the air chamber and service area

38:19.958 --> 38:24.208
with pipes, supply boxes,
electrical equipment, and sanitation.

38:24.708 --> 38:26.708
[energetic music continues]

38:28.916 --> 38:31.875
Once inside, there'll be
a wall of concrete blocks

38:31.875 --> 38:33.500
that secure the antechamber.

38:33.500 --> 38:35.875
Which then leads us to the vault.

38:38.125 --> 38:41.000
Then, we will cut the iron joints
that connect the blocks.

38:41.000 --> 38:44.333
[Berlin] <i>But we won't move
those blocks yet. And why is that, Damian?</i>

38:44.333 --> 38:47.166
Because inside the antechamber is CCTV,

38:47.166 --> 38:51.166
<i>which is linked directly to the monitors
of the security guards inside.</i>

38:51.666 --> 38:54.750
The guards will be bored
because there's no auction at the moment.

38:54.750 --> 38:55.666
Very bored.

38:55.666 --> 38:58.291
One guard at the main entrance,

38:58.291 --> 39:01.916
and a second one in the basement,
right in front of the vault.

39:01.916 --> 39:05.208
Here again, we can observe
the magnitude of our plan.

39:05.208 --> 39:09.500
Breaking into a vault when it's empty.
Don't you think that's a magnificent idea?

39:09.500 --> 39:11.500
It will optimize the chances of success.

39:11.500 --> 39:13.250
And that's why we need to get those guards

39:13.250 --> 39:15.625
away from their monitors
for three minutes.

39:16.833 --> 39:19.625
That's the minimum amount of time
I'll need to hack the CCTV.

39:19.625 --> 39:21.083
And how do we do it?

39:21.083 --> 39:23.416
Using diversionary tactics.

39:23.416 --> 39:25.041
<i>And for that, we'll need to know</i>

39:25.041 --> 39:28.250
<i>everything there is
to know about our new friends.</i>

39:28.875 --> 39:31.875
[Berlin] <i>We're going to analyze
every move these gentlemen make.</i>

39:31.875 --> 39:35.958
<i>But first, we must study the foundation
of every security guard's life.</i>

39:36.708 --> 39:37.833
What they eat for dinner.

39:37.833 --> 39:41.166
I'd like to place an order, please.
Two 14-inch pepperoni pizzas.

39:41.166 --> 39:43.708
At eight, they order food
using the landline.

39:44.208 --> 39:46.041
- Yes?
- So, what you order us?

39:46.041 --> 39:47.958
Pepperoni. [chuckles]

39:47.958 --> 39:49.375
- Pizza.
- Almost always pizza.

39:49.375 --> 39:52.208
[Damián] <i>The landline network interface
is located in the service area.</i>

39:52.208 --> 39:55.083
<i>Keila will have already hacked into
the system.</i>

39:55.083 --> 39:56.166
[phone ringing]

39:57.333 --> 39:58.833
[dialing]

39:59.708 --> 40:01.583
- Psst!
- [line ringing]

40:01.583 --> 40:03.541
- Good evening. How can I help you?
- [guard] <i>Hi.</i>

40:03.541 --> 40:06.750
I'd like to order
two 14-inch pepperoni pizzas

40:06.750 --> 40:07.750
<i>and two beers, please.</i>

40:07.750 --> 40:09.541
Perfect. And your address?

40:09.541 --> 40:11.791
Auction House Chez Viénot.

40:11.791 --> 40:14.375
<i>Fourteen Turenne Street.</i>

40:14.375 --> 40:15.916
Thank you and have a good night.

40:15.916 --> 40:17.208
Thank you.

40:17.208 --> 40:18.958
And so begins our show.

40:18.958 --> 40:21.541
In the service area,
we will have a changing zone.

40:21.541 --> 40:24.833
<i>There, we will remove all clothes
covered in dirt from the catacombs</i>

40:24.833 --> 40:26.750
<i>and put on our hazmat suits.</i>

40:26.750 --> 40:30.958
I don't want anyone in the antechamber
or the vault without their suit or gloves.

40:30.958 --> 40:32.833
<i>A fingerprint or a speck of dirt,</i>

40:32.833 --> 40:34.833
<i>even an eyelash will have your DNA.</i>

40:34.833 --> 40:36.750
And then, it's game over for us.

40:36.750 --> 40:38.750
[tense music playing]

40:38.750 --> 40:41.000
We'll use that time
to finish our preparations.

40:41.000 --> 40:43.083
<i>But mostly, we'll use the time...</i>

40:43.083 --> 40:44.750
You took 90 minutes?

40:44.750 --> 40:46.791
...to piss off the security guards.

40:48.875 --> 40:49.750
Cold food.

40:49.750 --> 40:52.250
They're not pepperoni,
and they're fuckin' cold.

40:52.250 --> 40:53.541
The wrong order.

40:53.541 --> 40:55.291
And they're not 14-inch.

40:55.291 --> 40:56.625
It's lemonade!

40:56.625 --> 40:59.375
The kind of things that really get
on your nerves when you're hungry.

40:59.375 --> 41:00.708
I'm not paying for this.

41:00.708 --> 41:01.791
[scoffs]

41:01.791 --> 41:03.291
You're not gonna pay?

41:04.166 --> 41:06.708
You're gonna pay me now.
Then you can go back to your hole.

41:06.708 --> 41:08.458
Got that, chipmunk?

41:08.458 --> 41:11.416
- Huh? [clicks tongue]
- [Berlin] <i>You're hungry. You're annoyed.</i>

41:11.416 --> 41:14.000
You've waited over an hour and a half.
The delivery guy's a punk.

41:14.000 --> 41:15.958
He's rude,
and he has that look in his eye.

41:15.958 --> 41:17.708
- What?
-"What? What?"

41:17.708 --> 41:18.875
You deaf too?

41:18.875 --> 41:22.291
He'll call his colleague downstairs,
and that's what we want him to do.

41:27.875 --> 41:30.208
Get up here. We've got a problem.

41:30.791 --> 41:32.083
A problem? What's going on?

41:32.083 --> 41:34.125
As soon as the second guard
leaves his post,

41:34.125 --> 41:37.125
that is precisely when
our second act will start.

41:38.333 --> 41:40.583
[suspenseful music playing]

41:54.833 --> 41:55.791
We're good to go.

41:55.791 --> 41:58.416
We'll have exactly three minutes
to complete the hack.

41:58.416 --> 41:59.500
[Keila] It's too short.

42:00.166 --> 42:01.250
It's really risky.

42:02.083 --> 42:05.583
My dear Keila,
where you see risk, I see adrenaline.

42:05.583 --> 42:07.333
[suspenseful music continues]

42:14.333 --> 42:16.041
Okay, Alain. On my way.

42:20.375 --> 42:22.958
- [Roi] Go.
- We extract the concrete block.

42:22.958 --> 42:24.833
<i>Like a piece of jigsaw puzzle.</i>

42:27.833 --> 42:29.458
[Damián] <i>And we get
inside the antechamber.</i>

42:29.458 --> 42:32.250
Naturally, the CCTV <i>will</i> see you.

42:32.250 --> 42:34.000
[energetic music playing]

42:35.625 --> 42:36.625
[Bruce scoffs]

42:37.750 --> 42:38.791
[Berlin] <i>But Bruce...</i>

42:38.791 --> 42:40.416
You called the other monkey for help?

42:40.416 --> 42:43.875
...playing the cocky delivery guy,
will make sure you go under the radar.

42:43.875 --> 42:45.416
Hey. Don't touch me.

42:45.416 --> 42:48.291
You understand anything,
or do I have to speak monkey?

42:48.291 --> 42:49.500
Hmm? Huh?

42:52.416 --> 42:53.375
There's a door there.

42:54.375 --> 42:56.541
I know. It's our Achilles' heel.

42:56.541 --> 42:58.833
If someone opens that door, we're screwed.

42:58.833 --> 43:01.416
In our line of work, there's always
a certain percentage of risk.

43:02.625 --> 43:04.416
Two minutes, 30 seconds left.

43:06.833 --> 43:09.375
You need to buy us
as much time as possible.

43:09.875 --> 43:11.000
[imitating chimp]

43:11.000 --> 43:13.166
[Berlin] <i>You need to push them
until they blow a fuse.</i>

43:13.166 --> 43:15.000
Alain, Alain. Take it easy.

43:15.750 --> 43:17.166
- I like this.
- Don't you touch that.

43:18.208 --> 43:20.833
[Damián] <i>And while Bruce
buys us some precious time,</i>

43:20.833 --> 43:23.333
<i>Keila and I will neutralize the CCTV.</i>

43:23.333 --> 43:26.000
Keila, would you kindly explain
the technological details?

43:26.000 --> 43:27.666
The antechamber is a security room.

43:27.666 --> 43:28.750
<i>It holds the hard disks</i>

43:28.750 --> 43:30.958
<i>for the auction house's
entire security system.</i>

43:31.541 --> 43:33.416
<i>- I'll hack the four cameras we need.</i>
- [beeps]

43:33.416 --> 43:34.916
[Keila] <i>The main hall.</i>

43:36.041 --> 43:37.833
Now? Will you pay me?

43:40.375 --> 43:42.583
- [Keila] <i>The antechamber.</i>
- [monitor beeps]

43:42.583 --> 43:45.208
- You wanna fight?
- [guard] Hey. He's not worth it.

43:45.916 --> 43:47.000
Calm down.

43:49.166 --> 43:50.166
Ninety seconds left.

43:52.291 --> 43:53.291
[Keila] <i>Outside the vault.</i>

43:55.750 --> 43:57.833
- Hey! Get away from there.
- Pay me, then!

43:57.833 --> 43:59.458
[Keila] <i>And inside the vault.</i>

44:01.000 --> 44:02.416
[monitor humming]

44:03.125 --> 44:04.875
[sounds distort]

44:04.875 --> 44:07.208
[Keila] There was another wire.
I didn't see it. [gasps]

44:07.208 --> 44:09.333
You just blew out the CCTV.

44:10.541 --> 44:12.583
- [stopwatch clicking]
- [gasps softly]

44:12.583 --> 44:14.041
[breathing shakily]

44:15.375 --> 44:17.833
Hey. Are you okay? Kid?

44:17.833 --> 44:20.958
Once you're finally knocked out
and lying on the floor,

44:20.958 --> 44:22.750
you can bite on the fizzy pill.

44:22.750 --> 44:26.125
And soon, you'll be spitting foam
from the mouth like a rabid dog.

44:26.125 --> 44:27.666
And what if they call an ambulance?

44:27.666 --> 44:28.666
Or the police?

44:28.666 --> 44:30.083
- And what would they say?
- Wake up.

44:30.083 --> 44:32.666
[Berlin] <i>"We beat up some delivery guy
because the pizza was cold,</i>

44:32.666 --> 44:34.833
<i>and he fell on his head,
and he's having a seizure?"</i>

44:34.833 --> 44:36.791
Don't worry. They'll revive him first.

44:36.791 --> 44:39.416
Alain! A cushion. Quick! Quick!

44:39.416 --> 44:40.583
Seventy-five seconds.

44:40.583 --> 44:41.916
I blew a fuse.

44:41.916 --> 44:44.875
Relax. Find the fuse, then bypass it.

44:44.875 --> 44:45.958
I don't see it.

44:45.958 --> 44:47.625
- I can't find it!
- The fuse box.

44:47.625 --> 44:48.958
Open it!

44:48.958 --> 44:50.291
Find the fuse.

44:50.291 --> 44:51.416
One minute.

44:52.041 --> 44:53.291
[Keila] Found it!

44:53.291 --> 44:54.875
Too many. We have no time. Leave it.

44:54.875 --> 44:57.416
If we leave, they'll catch us.
The cameras are dead.

44:58.125 --> 44:59.083
A spoon!

45:02.333 --> 45:03.583
[quietly] Come on.

45:07.333 --> 45:09.041
[guard]
Open up! Come on! Come on!

45:09.041 --> 45:10.250
Fifty seconds.

45:12.583 --> 45:13.541
[guard] Come on.

45:13.541 --> 45:14.875
Come on. That's it.

45:16.333 --> 45:17.708
Thirty seconds.

45:17.708 --> 45:18.750
[softly] C'mon.

45:20.708 --> 45:22.083
I got it.

45:27.750 --> 45:29.583
- [inhales sharply]
- Water!

45:32.791 --> 45:34.000
Here.

45:34.500 --> 45:36.291
[splutters and moans]

45:36.791 --> 45:38.166
Come on. Come on!

45:38.166 --> 45:40.750
Fifteen seconds. Fuck's sake. Hurry.

45:41.958 --> 45:43.958
[Keila panting]

45:45.000 --> 45:45.875
[electricity crackles]

45:45.875 --> 45:46.791
[monitor beeps]

45:46.791 --> 45:48.916
[guard] C'mon. Hey! Come on. Get up.

45:48.916 --> 45:50.916
- Okay. That's it. Okay.
- What happened?

45:50.916 --> 45:53.083
- Stand up. Up you go.
- What's goin' on? Where am I?

45:53.083 --> 45:54.333
That's it. Up you get.

45:54.333 --> 45:55.708
[Roi on earpiece] <i>Five seconds.</i>

45:55.708 --> 45:56.750
Get out, now.

45:56.750 --> 45:58.125
Shut up, Roi.

45:58.708 --> 45:59.583
[electricity crackles]

45:59.583 --> 46:00.541
Done!

46:00.541 --> 46:01.625
[electricity humming]

46:01.625 --> 46:03.000
Here. Take that.

46:03.708 --> 46:07.458
- For the pizza.
- There we go. You'll be fine. All right.

46:07.458 --> 46:09.500
- [stopwatch ticking]
- That's it. Out of time.

46:09.500 --> 46:11.083
You gotta leave. Get out.

46:11.083 --> 46:13.208
- Leave. I'll do it.
- Almost done.

